own that\nthe evolution of simulated 1D radial density profiles closely resembles the\nThomson scattering electron density measurements in MAST. An intuitive\nexplanation for the origin of the measured density structures is proposed,\nbased upon the results of the toroidal Hall-MHD simulations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 13 Aug 2013 13:18:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-03-04"}
